Steps to Install AutoGen Studio on a Mac:

1. Download Anaconda from https://www.anaconda.com/download
2. Go to  Finder —> open Terminal. Type the following 4 commands (one by one) in the Terminal:

conda create -n ag python=3.11

conda activate ag

pip install autogenstudio

autogenstudio ui --port 8081


Explanation: First command creates a new conda environment. Second command activates the conda environment. Third command installs autogenstudio. Fourth command runs autogenstudio on port 8081 (Note: you can change the port number eg to 8082 or 8083)

Note: You will get the following message:

Uvicorn running on http://127.0.0.1:8081 

3.Copy that local URL in your browser (or hold Command and click on the link to open it) —> This will open Autogen studio UI:

